During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki introduced Secretary of Agriculture Tom Vilsack as a special guest. Secretary Vilsack discussed the importance of food and nutrition security, highlighting the impact of the American Rescue Plan in reducing hunger in the United States. He also outlined the three key investments for nutrition and food security in the American Families Plan, which include providing nutrition assistance for children during the summer months, expanding free school meals in high-poverty areas, and investing in strategies to improve the nutritional value of school meals. Secretary Vilsack also addressed questions about a copper mine project, reforming the Thrifty Food Plan, COVID loan forgiveness for farmers, and the timeline for implementing the American Families Plan. Psaki also addressed questions about social media platforms, the debt limit, police reform, and the Tokyo Olympics.